## Revoke Tokens

> Example Request

```shell
curl "<%= config.host %>/client/revoke-tokens" \
  -H "<%= config.auth %>" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "identifier": "Bk0zwVx1Z",
    "clientToken": "566595c8ce88ccec69328566c8ce8595c8"
  }'
```

> Example Response

```json
{
  "success": true
}
```

Revokes client SSO and access tokens associated with either a client or client SSO token.
When a token is revoked, it can no longer be used to access the Biller Direct API.

Either a client `identifier` or `clientToken` must be provided.
If a client `identifier` is provided, all current SSO and access tokens associated with that client will be revoked.
If a `clientToken` from [Create Token](#create-token) is provided, that token and any related access tokens will be revoked.
If both parameters are passed, the `clientToken` parameter is ignored.

### HTTP Request

`POST <%= config.host %>/client/revoke-tokens`

### Arguments

Parameter | Description
----- | -----------
`identifier` | Optional A unique identifier that represents a user in your system.
`clientToken` | Optional The client SSO token produced by a call to [Create Token](#create-token).

### Returns

Returns an object with a `success` property.
